cs.SE, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses guidelines for conducting Multivocal Literature Reviews (MLRs) in Software Engineering (SE), which involves including both published and grey literature. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the search process and source quality assessment, which are related to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Digital Libraries (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper discusses the reporting of the review, which is related to Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
